When running on a JIRA OnDemand only instance, if the user tries to import a JIRA export that has users that aren't members of any group, the 'com.atlassian.studio.jira.haup.UserCreationListener' class will blindly try to grant access to every user.
Failing to do so it will spam the administrators with an email for each failed grant operation.

We should verify if the user is a valid JIRA user before trying to grant access to JIRA OnDemand while the import operation is running.

